      • areEquivalent

        public static boolean areEquivalent(TypeReference a,
                    TypeReference b)
        Returns whether two type references refer to the same type. Note that a parameterized type will not match its corresponding raw type (but a generic definition will match its raw type).
        Parameters:
        a - The first type reference.
        b - The second type reference.
        Returns:
        true if two type references refer to the same type; otherwise, false.

      • areEquivalent

        public static boolean areEquivalent(TypeReference a,
                    TypeReference b,
                    boolean strict)
        Returns whether two type references refer to the same type.
        Parameters:
        a - The first type reference.
        b - The second type reference.
        strict - If true, a parameterized type will not match its corresponding raw type (but a generic definition will match its raw type).
        Returns:
        true if two type references refer to the same type; otherwise, false.
